      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KIARNI PHOENIX (2) comes off an average effort last start when fifth at Maitland over 450m behind Cessnock Curtain (25.59) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money the start prior. Should bounce back. SUNBURNT KEEPER (8) has a strong record here with three wins and two placings from seven starts. Placed last time (29.81) at The Gardens in a Grade 5, finishing third and beaten 6 lengths. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. IT'S A GLAM (5) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at Wentworth Park, but was among the placings at The Gardens three back. Has the ability and can find best this time. SEE RED (4) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
